> Example Request:

```shell
curl https://api.smartsheet.com/2.0/sheets/{sheetId}/rows \
-H "Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN" \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-X POST \
-d '{ \
    "sendTo": [ \
        {"email": "recipient@smartsheet.com"} \
    ], \
    "subject": "some subject", \
    "message": "some message", \
    "ccMe": false, \
    "rowIds": [ \
        rId1, \
        rId2 \
    ], \
    "columnIds": [ \
        cId1, \
        cId2 \
    ], \
    "includeAttachments": false, \
    "includeDiscussions": false \
}'
```

> Example Response:

```json
{
  "resultCode": 0,
    "message": "SUCCESS"
}
```

`POST /sheets/{sheetId}/rows/emails`

Sends one or more Rows via email.

     |     |
-----|-----|
<%= SCOPE %> | SHARE_SHEETS
<%= HEADERS %> | <%= HEADER_AUTH %><br/><%= HEADER_CT_JSON %>
<%= REQUEST %> | [MultiRowEmail object](#multirowemail-object). If **columnIds** is null, all columns except hidden columns shall be included. If it is empty, no columns shall be included: if empty, either **includeAttachments** or **includeDiscussions** must be specified.
<%= RETURNS %> | [Result object](#result-object)
